    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "I could see it being useful to have a way for packages to identify the correct way to cite the package in literature and to have Spack be able to produce a bibtex file for a given set of packages.\r\n\r\n```\r\nspack -cite foo\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould produce a bibtex file (or equiv.) for foo and all its dependencies.\r\n\r\nThis would probably require a new package directive such as\r\n\r\n```\r\nciting(author = 'Jean C\u00e9sar', title = 'An amazing title', year = '2013',\r\n    month = 'jan', volume = '12', pages = '12--23', journal = 'Nice Journal')\r\n```",
    "performed_via_github_app": null
}